            . On the evening of the 26th of December, I was in <placeName id="t18210110-38-crimeloc224">Oxford-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18210110-38-crimeloc224" type="placeName" value="Oxford-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18210110-38-crimeloc224" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210110-38-off222 t18210110-38-crimeloc224"></join> and felt a hand in my pocket, turned round, and found the prisoner close by my pocket; I collared him, looked down, and found my handkerchief at his feet - I had not dropped it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210110-38-person387">
                  WILLIAM 
                  MALLAGHAN
               <interp inst="t18210110-38-person387" type="surname" value="MALLAGHAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210110-38-person387" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210110-38-person387" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an Excise officer. I was with Mead, we stopped to look at a fight. I saw him collar the prisoner, who dropped the handkerchief; I am positive of it.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was knocked against the gentleman, and he collared me.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18210110-38-verdict225" type="verdictDescription">
